{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> μεθύω</b> [ῠ], <br /> (μέθυ), only <i>present</i> and <i>imperfect</i>: <i>future</i> and <i>aorist</i> <i>active</i> belong to μεθύσκω (μεθύσας is <i>falsa lectio</i> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.AD(?): Nonnus Epicus “Dionysiaca” 28.211 \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]; μεθύσαντας is <i>falsa lectio</i> for -τες in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.239a), \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<i>aorist</i> being supplied by <i>passive</i> of μεθύσκω:— <b>to be drunken with wine</b>, νευστάζων κεφαλῇ, μεθύοντι ἐοικώς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 18.240 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; μεθύων, opposed to νήφων, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 478, 627, compare 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus “Supp.” 4.12, 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “Fragmenta.” 128, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 1048, “PHal.” 1.193 (3rd c.BC), etc.\">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]; μ. ὑπὸ τοῦ οἴνου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Symposium” 2.26 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ μεθύειν <b>drunkenness</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Antiphanes Comicus 187.2, 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor 43; τὸ μ. πημονῆς λυτήριον 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 758. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>metaphorically</i>, <br /><Level3><b>__II.1</b></Level3> of things, <b>to be drenched, steeped</b> in any liquid, with <i>dative</i>, e.g. βοείην.. μεθύουσαν ἀλοιφῇ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 17.390; μεθύων ἐλαίῳ λύχνος 2nd c.AD: Babrius Fabularum Scriptor 114.1; [χείμαρρος] ὄμβροισι μ. “Anthologia Graeca” 9.277 (1st c.AD: Antiphilus Epigrammaticus). \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> of persons, <b>to be intoxicated</b> with passion, pride, etc., ὑπὸ τῆς Ἀφροδίτης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Symposium” 8.21; ὑπὸ τρυφῆς 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Critias” 121a; ἔρωτι 6th c.BC: Anacreon Lyricus 19; τῷ μεγέθει τῶν πεπραγμένων 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 4.49; περὶ τὰς ἡδονάς 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “Vitae Sophistarum” 1.22.1; οὐ μ. τὴν φρόνησιν 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor 301; μ. τὸ φίλημα “Anthologia Graeca” 5.304. \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>] <br /><Level4><b>__II.2.b</b></Level4> <b>to be stupefied, stunned</b>, πληγαῖς μεθύων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 22.98; ἐξ ὀδυνάων 2nd-3rd c.AD: Oppianus Anazarbensis Epicus “Halieutica - Poetae Bucolici et Didactici” 5.228, cf. Nonn.[same place] \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G3184","accentedUnicode":"μεθύω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0271","matchingForm":"ἀμέθυστος","stepTransliteration":"amethustos","gloss":"amethyst","_zh_tw_Gloss":"紫晶","_es_Gloss":"amatista","_zh_Gloss":"紫晶"},{"strongNumber":"G3178","matchingForm":"μέθη","stepTransliteration":"methē","gloss":"drunkenness","_zh_tw_Gloss":"醉酒","_es_Gloss":"embriaguez","_zh_Gloss":"醉酒"},{"strongNumber":"G3182","matchingForm":"μεθύσκω","stepTransliteration":"methuskō","gloss":"to get drunk","_zh_tw_Gloss":"醉了的人, 醉酒","_es_Gloss":"embriagarse","_zh_Gloss":"醉了的人, 醉酒"},{"strongNumber":"G3183","matchingForm":"μέθυσος","stepTransliteration":"methusos","gloss":"drunkard","_zh_tw_Gloss":"醉酒","_es_Gloss":"borracho","_zh_Gloss":"醉酒"}],"shortDef":"to get drunk","mediumDef":"to get drunk <br /><b>to be intoxicated, be drunk,</b> <ref='Mat.24.49'>Mt. 24:49</ref>; <ref='Act.2.15'>Acts 2:15;</ref> <ref='1Co.11.21'>1Cor. 11:21;</ref> <ref='1Th.5.7'>1Thess. 5:7;</ref> <ref='Rev.17.6'>Rev. 17:6</ref>*","stepGloss":"to get drunk","stepTransliteration":"methuō","count":6,"_es_Definition":"estar borracho ; tal vez beber mucho (JN.2:10)","_zh_tw_Definition":"喝醉","_zh_Definition":"喝醉","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"say khướt; phường say sưa","_